
<div id='example1' class='rounded-md bg-gray-100 my-3 p-3'>
  <h4 class='text-xl font-medium mb-8'>A - Loop through all tables and show row count</h4>

  <div class='p-4 border border-gray-400 rounded-lg bg-gray-300'>
    <div>
      <%= link_to 'Show tables row count', count_all_home_index_path, class: 'my-2 text-white bg-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-800 focus:ring-4 focus:ring-blue-300 font-medium rounded-lg text-sm px-3 py-1.5 focus:outline-none', data: { turbo_frame: 'modal_frame' } %>
      <p class='text-gray-500 my-2'>1. Normal option: using the <code class='text-pink-600'>Main Modal</code> ({ turbo_frame: 'modal_frame' })</p>
    </div>
    <hr class='border-gray-400' />
    <div class='mt-3'>
      <%= link_to 'Show tables row count', count_all_home_index_path, class: 'my-2 focus:outline-none text-white bg-red-700 hover:bg-red-800 focus:ring-4 focus:ring-red-300 font-medium rounded-lg text-sm px-3 py-1.5', data: { turbo_frame: 'modal_frame', 'disable-on-request': true, 'show-modal-when-response': 'true' } %>
      <p class='text-gray-500 my-2'>2. Disable button on request and show the <code class='text-pink-600'>Main Modal</code> ({ turbo_frame: 'modal_frame' }) when server response</p>
    </div>
    <hr class='border-gray-400' />
    <div class='mt-3'>
      <%= link_to 'Show tables row count', count_all_home_index_path, class: 'my-2 focus:outline-none text-white bg-yellow-400 hover:bg-yellow-500 focus:ring-4 focus:ring-yellow-300 font-medium rounded-lg text-sm px-3 py-1.5', data: { turbo_frame: 'modal_frame', 'disable-on-request': true } %>
      <p class='text-gray-500 my-2'>3. Disable button on request and show the <code class='text-pink-600'>Main Modal</code> ({ turbo_frame: 'modal_frame' }) when click</p>
    </div>
    <hr class='border-gray-400' />
    <div class='mt-3'>
      <%= link_to 'Show tables row count button inside modal', count_all_in_modal_home_index_path, class: 'my-2 text-white bg-green-700 hover:bg-green-800 focus:outline-none focus:ring-4 focus:ring-green-300 font-medium rounded-lg text-sm px-3 py-1.5 text-center', data: { turbo_frame: 'modal_frame' } %>
      <p class='text-gray-500 my-2'>4. Show button in the <code class='text-pink-600'>Main Modal</code> ({ turbo_frame: 'modal_frame' }), when click the button, show the <code class='text-pink-600'>Sub Modal</code> ({ turbo_frame: 'sub_modal_frame' })</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div id='example2' class='rounded-md bg-gray-100 my-3 p-3'>
  <h4 class='text-xl font-medium mb-8'>B - Form without validation</h4>
  <div class='grid grid-cols-2 gap-3'>
    <div>
      <div class='p-4 mb-4 text-blue-800 border border-blue-300 rounded-lg bg-blue-100'>
        <%= render 'home/partials/sample_post_form', data_options: { 'show-modal-when-response': 'true' } %>
      </div>
      <p class='text-gray-500'>1. When submit the form, the button will be disabled, and when server response,
      both error status and success status will be shown in the modal</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class='p-4 mb-4 text-green-800 border border-green-300 rounded-lg bg-green-100'>
        <%= render 'home/partials/test_submit_form', locals: { frame_id: 'sub_modal_frame' } %>
      </div>
      <p class='text-gray-500'>2. When submit the form, the button will be disabled, and the modal will show loading spinner,
      and when server response, both error status and success status will be shown in the modal</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class='p-4 mb-4 text-blue-800 border border-blue-300 rounded-lg bg-blue-100'>
        <%= render 'home/partials/test_replace_the_form1' %>
      </div>
      <p class='text-gray-500'>3. When submit the form, the button will be disabled, and when server response,
        if error the modal will show, else replace the form</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class='p-4 mb-4 text-blue-800 border border-blue-300 rounded-lg bg-blue-100'>
        <%= render 'home/partials/test_replace_the_form2' %>
      </div>
      <p class='text-gray-500'>4. When submit the form, the button will be disabled, and the modal will show loading spinner,
        and when server response, if error the modal will show, else replace the form</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div id='example3' class='rounded-md bg-gray-100 p-3'>
  <h4 class='text-xl font-medium mb-8'>C - Form inside modal without validation</h4>

  <div class='grid grid-cols-2 gap-3'>
    <div class='p-4 mb-4 text-blue-800 border border-blue-300 rounded-lg bg-blue-100'>
      <%= link_to 'Inside modal 1', sample_post_inside_modal1_home_index_path, class: 'text-white bg-gray-500 hover:bg-gray-600 focus:ring-4 focus:outline-none focus:ring-gray-300 font-medium rounded-lg text-sm px-3 py-1.5 text-center', data: { turbo_frame: 'modal_frame' } %>
      <p class='text-gray-500 my-2'>1. Like the <code class='text-pink-600'>B - Form without validation 2.</code>, but open form inside the <code class='text-pink-600'>Main Modal</code>, when submit the form,
      the <code class='text-pink-600'>Sub Modal</code> will show loading spinner, and when server response,
        both error status and success status will be shown in the modal</p>
    </div>
    <div class='p-4 mb-4 text-blue-800 border border-blue-300 rounded-lg bg-blue-100'>
      <%= link_to 'Inside modal 2', sample_post_inside_modal2_home_index_path, class: 'focus:outline-none text-white bg-yellow-400 hover:bg-yellow-500 focus:ring-4 focus:ring-yellow-300 font-medium rounded-lg text-sm px-3 py-1.5', data: { turbo_frame: 'modal_frame' } %>
      <p class='text-gray-500 my-2'>Like the <code class='text-pink-600'>C 1.</code>, but sleep 3 seconds before response the form when click the link</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

